83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
SENATE AMENDMENTS TO
SENATE BILL 1590
By COMMITTEE ON NATURAL RESOURCES AND WILDFIRE
February 13
1 Delete lines 16 through 19 of the printed bill and insert:
2 “(b) Is being transferred for a specific infrastructure, utility, transportation, conservation or
3 recreational use;
4 “(c) Consists primarily of one or more surplus federal buildings;
5 “(d) Is held in trust or for the benefit of a federally recognized Indian tribe in Oregon or a
6 member of a tribe;
7 “(e) Is acquired by the Department of State Lands in lieu of lands granted under the Act of
8 February 14, 1859 (11 Stat. 383); or
9 “(f) Consists solely of timber, minerals or other resources.
10 “(4) This section does not prohibit actions taken by a public body to protect a legitimate public
11 body property right or interest, to resolve any cloud on a title connected to the public body or to
12 conduct activities otherwise required under state law.”.
13 In line 20, delete “2029” and insert “2032”.
